WEBVTT

00:00:01.139 --> 00:00:04.179
What is envy? Do you know?

00:00:04.179 --> 00:00:08.820
It's important that we be able to identify the symptoms of envy.

00:00:08.820 --> 00:00:14.019
Why? Because envy is an expression

00:00:14.019 --> 00:00:17.420
of hatred. It's an enemy of peace

00:00:17.420 --> 00:00:22.339
and if left unchecked, it can result in spiritual

00:00:22.339 --> 00:00:26.359
death. As described in the Bible,

00:00:26.359 --> 00:00:31.059
envy has two symptoms. The first is probably more

00:00:31.059 --> 00:00:38.020
familiar, an envious person wants what someone else has.

00:00:38.020 --> 00:00:43.939
It's the second symptom that makes envy especially dangerous.

00:00:43.939 --> 00:00:49.100
An envious person not only wants what someone else has,

00:00:49.100 --> 00:00:53.100
he doesn't want the other person to have it.

00:00:53.100 --> 00:00:56.820
Here's an example. In the first century,

00:00:56.820 --> 00:01:00.100
Jewish religious leaders envy Jesus

00:01:00.100 --> 00:01:05.219
because Jesus was much appreciated by the common people.

00:01:05.219 --> 00:01:09.140
Jesus dealt with people, including lolley ones,

00:01:09.140 --> 00:01:12.459
in a way that dignified them. As a result,

00:01:12.459 --> 00:01:15.060
he was appreciated.

00:01:15.060 --> 00:01:17.859
The religious leaders envied him,

00:01:17.859 --> 00:01:22.819
but rather than adjusting their own way of dealing with people,

00:01:22.819 --> 00:01:29.939
they attacked Jesus verbally in an effort to destroy his good reputation.

00:01:29.939 --> 00:01:33.459
They spread malicious slander.

00:01:33.459 --> 00:01:37.140
Not only did they want what Jesus had,

00:01:37.140 --> 00:01:40.340
they didn't want Jesus to have it.

00:01:40.340 --> 00:01:44.579
No wonder envy is listed as one of the works of the flush

00:01:44.579 --> 00:01:48.819
in Galatians chapter 5 verse 21.

00:01:48.819 --> 00:01:55.680
It's a dangerous quality that we need to avoid.

00:01:55.680 --> 00:02:01.659
How does envy disrupt peace?

00:02:01.659 --> 00:02:09.259
Envy undermines damages or even destroys relationships

00:02:09.259 --> 00:02:13.659
in the family and in the congregation.

00:02:13.659 --> 00:02:20.219
Consider the example of Jacob and his 12 sons.

00:02:20.219 --> 00:02:26.219
Jacob had special affection for one of his sons, Joseph.

00:02:26.219 --> 00:02:29.500
As a result, Joseph's brothers became envious.

00:02:29.580 --> 00:02:35.099
How did the envy manifest itself? What was the fruitage?

00:02:35.099 --> 00:02:37.419
Well, they dealt treacherously with Joseph

00:02:37.419 --> 00:02:41.580
selling him into slavery. And as if that weren't bad enough,

00:02:41.580 --> 00:02:46.460
they compounded their wrong by lying to Jacob,

00:02:46.460 --> 00:02:49.900
telling him that Joseph was dead.

00:02:49.900 --> 00:02:56.379
According to the Bible account, Jacob refused to be comforted.

00:02:56.379 --> 00:03:03.740
He mourned Joseph for years. What a terrible consequence of envy.

00:03:03.740 --> 00:03:11.419
It's clear that envy allows no room for love, compassion, or kindness.

00:03:11.419 --> 00:03:14.699
Those qualities go out the window.

00:03:14.699 --> 00:03:19.819
And they're replaced by qualities such as a hatred,

00:03:19.819 --> 00:03:28.060
strife, fits of anger. Can envy disrupt the peace of a congregation?

00:03:28.219 --> 00:03:31.580
Consider the examples of Korah, Daithun, and Abairun.

00:03:32.460 --> 00:03:37.979
They envied Moses and Aaron in the congregation of Israel.

00:03:40.219 --> 00:03:42.939
How did that envy manifest itself?

00:03:43.740 --> 00:03:47.580
Well, they began to speak negatively, critically of Jehovah's

00:03:47.580 --> 00:03:51.740
representatives, even accusing Moses of playing the prince

00:03:51.740 --> 00:03:54.460
and lifting himself up above the others.

00:03:55.340 --> 00:04:01.419
They forgot that Jehovah had put Moses and Aaron

00:04:01.419 --> 00:04:03.580
in their positions of responsibility.

00:04:04.780 --> 00:04:09.740
How did Jehovah react to that manifestation of envy?

00:04:11.259 --> 00:04:15.500
He destroyed those three men and all who supported them

00:04:15.500 --> 00:04:18.459
for a time the congregation was robbed of its peace,

00:04:19.339 --> 00:04:23.899
and the account certainly provides some insight into Jehovah's view

00:04:24.540 --> 00:04:30.220
of envy. Now, by this point, you're no doubt thinking I would never want

00:04:30.220 --> 00:04:34.939
something so badly that I would damage someone else to get it,

00:04:36.699 --> 00:04:40.060
but we're all imperfect. We have a treacherous heart,

00:04:41.100 --> 00:04:45.899
and envy is insidious. In the following dramatization,

00:04:46.459 --> 00:04:50.620
notice how envy threatens to disrupt peace.

